On Sep 22, 2009, at 2:51 PM, oliver.riches@... wrote:

&gt;  So therefore REST service suffer from exactly the same problems as  
&gt; SOAP services with versioning - breaking changes...

Well...the nature of the problem is the same (if one communication  
partner changes the language communication is harmed) but REST is an  
improvement because it makes fragmented change much easier. E.g. a  
server can add elements to HTML without breaking any clients or Amazon  
can change the state machine of its Web application even *while* you  
are in the middle of making a purchase.

Jan



